{{Infobox power station |name =Dobrich Wind Farm |image = |image_caption = |location =[[Dobrin, Bulgaria|Dobrin]] |owner =[[Balkan Energy]] |status =Proposed |ps_units_operational=100 |ps_electrical_capacity= 200 [[Watt#Megawatt|MW]] |commissioned = |decommissioned = }} The '''Dobrin Wind Farm''' ({{lang-bg|Вятърна перка Дроб}}) is a proposed wind power project in [[Dobrin, Bulgaria|Dobrin]], [[Dobrich Province]], [[Bulgaria]]. It will have 100 individual [[wind turbine]]s<ref>[http://www.ebrdrenewables.com/sites/renew/Lists/Projects/DispForm.aspx?ID=1874&Source=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eebrdrenewables%2Ecom%2Fsites%2Frenew%2Fcountries%2FBulgaria%2Fdefault%2Easpx Dobrich Wind Farm]</ref> with a nominal output of around 2 [[Watt#Megawatt|MW]] which will deliver up to 200 MW of power, enough to power over 79,800 homes, with a capital investment required of approximately US$180 million.
