'''Gadolinium oxyorthosilicate''' (known as GSO) is a type of [[Scintillator#Inorganic crystals|scintillating inorganic crystal]] used for imaging in [[nuclear medicine]] and for [[calorimetry]] in [[particle physics]].
The formula is Gd<sub>2</sub>SiO<sub>5</sub>. Its main properties are shown below:
