'''Kory Johnson''' is an American environmentalist from [[Arizona]]. 

In 1991, while still a young girl, Johnson led a successful effort by [[Children for a Safe Environment]] to stop a hazardous waste dump being built in her local area.  In 1996 she joined [[Greenpeace]] and helped organize protests against trainloads of [[DDT]]-contaminated dirt into Arizona.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=aIDw-iYghioC&pg=PA144&lpg=PA144&dq=%22Kory+Johnson%22+goldman&source=bl&ots=3-PXX3GuuS&sig=xL_hRRwrckBCVQh8yTt5eLgGals&hl=en&ei=g7ATSv6NCcaGkQX_6YWJDw&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=4#PPA144,M1  Women's Studies Quarterly, Spring/Summer 2001], p. 144.</ref>

She was awarded the [[Goldman Environmental Prize]] in 1998,<ref name="goldman">Goldman Environmental Prize: [http://www.goldmanprize.org/node/114 Kory Johnson] (Retrieved on November 27, 2007)</ref> for her efforts against toxic and [[radioactive contamination|nuclear contamination]].

