The '''Kot Addu Power Company Limited''' (KAPCO) owns, operates, and maintains a multi-[[Fossil fuel power station|fuel fired power plant]] in [[Kot Addu]], [[District Muzaffargarh]], [[Punjab (Pakistan)|Punjab]], [[Pakistan]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=10394635|title=Company Overview of Kot Addu Power Company Limited|last=|first=|date=|website=Bloomberg.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=19 November 2017}}</ref>
== History == Incorporated in 1996, the Kot Addu Power Plant was built by the [[Pakistan Water and Power Development Authority]] (WAPDA). In April, 2000, the company was incorporated as a public limited company.
== Activity == Kot Addu Power Plant produces 1,600 MW of electricity. On April 18, 2005 the Company was formally listed on all three Stock Exchanges of Pakistan.
== Governance == * CEO: Aftab Mahmood Butt * CFO: Mohtashim Aftab. == References == <references />
