A '''nutrition scale''' is a [[Weighing scale|weighing instrument]] that output precise [[nutritional information]] for foods or liquids. Most scales calculate [[calorie]]s, [[carbohydrate]]s, and [[fat]]s, with more sophisticated scales calculating additional nutrients such as [[Vitamin K]], [[potassium]], [[magnesium]], and [[sodium]].

Scales often use [[USDA]] information on food to ensure accuracy. The products are used primarily as a [[weight management]] tool, but have found a user base with [[Diabetes|diabetics]] and [[Hypertension|hypertensive]] people.

{{DEFAULTSORT:Nutritional Scale}}
[[Category:Weighing instruments]]

'''PyTEC''' is a containerised [[Pyrolysis]] Waste Disposal System designs by [[QinetiQ]] and used in various military applications.<ref>[http://www.theengineer.co.uk/Articles/313388/PyTEC+converts+waste+to+energy.htm PyTEC converts waste to energy]</ref> The system converts waste products to thermal energy which can be used for energy generation.
The system was developed by Compact Power Ltd specifically for QinetiQ. Compact Power's technology is now offered by Ethos Energy. The system was first fitted to [[HMS Ocean]]<ref>[http://publishing.yudu.com/Ab9xx/WTMay08/resources/6.htm?skipFlashCheck=true First fit of new pyrolsis system]</ref> and is currently under evaluation for the US Army.

