{{infobox non-profit | Non-profit_name = The Stony Brook–Millstone Watershed Association | Non-profit_logo = Stony Brook-Millstone Watershed Association logo adapted from a trail marker.jpg | Non-profit_type = | founded_date = 1949 | founder = | headquarters = [[Hopewell Township, Mercer County, New Jersey|Hopewell Township]], [[Mercer County, New Jersey|Mercer County]], [[New Jersey]], {{nowrap|United States}} | key_people = | area_served = Central New Jersey | focus = | method = | revenue = | endowment = | num_volunteers = | num_employees = | num_members = | Non-profit_slogan = "Your water. Your environment. Your voice." | homepage = {{URL|http://www.thewatershed.org/}} }}
The '''Stony Brook–Millstone Watershed Association''' is a [[New Jersey]] organization devoted to promoting and protecting the [[drainage basin|watershed]]s of [[Central Jersey|central New Jersey]]'s [[Stony Brook (Millstone River)|Stony Brook]] and [[Millstone River]], along with associated natural resources and beauty. Claiming to be central New Jersey's first environmental group, it was established in 1949. The organization promotes and advocates conservation and restoration of natural habitats, collects data on environmental conditions in its watersheds, and provides environmental education through numerous programs.
The association is centered on its 930-acre [[nature reserve]] in [[Hopewell Township, Mercer County, New Jersey|Hopewell Township]], [[Mercer County, New Jersey|Mercer County]], which includes portions of Stony Brook, a pond, several trails, the Watershed Center for environmental education, and the [[Stony Brook Millstone Watershed Arboretum]].<ref name="aboutus">{{cite web|url=http://thewatershed.org/about-us/ |title=About Us – The Stony Brook–Millstone Watershed Association |publisher=watershed.org |accessdate= September 17, 2014}}</ref>
